comments.body:
The issue here is rather clear. While we copy routes from host upstream interface to the container, there might be dependencies between routes, so, to keep things simple, we just retry to copy routes n times, with n number of routes. While doing this, we [don't consider `ENETUNREACH` and `EEXIST` as errors](https://passt.top/passt/tree/netlink.c?id=765eb0bf1651d20ca319eeb8b41ff35f52f2a29c#n658), because we might be trying inserting a route that we already added successfully, or one that doesn't have its route dependency satisfied yet. `ENETUNREACH` isn't enough, though: we also need to ignore `EHOSTUNREACH` ("no route to host"), because we might not have, at some point, a route to reach a given gateway.

However, just to be sure that's your case: could you please try to build passt (it's simple: `git clone git://passt.top/passt; make -C passt`) with the patch below (hacky and very lightly tested):

```
diff --git a/netlink.c b/netlink.c
index d3bea68..0465f1a 100644
--- a/netlink.c
+++ b/netlink.c
@@ -344,6 +344,27 @@ unsigned int nl_get_ext_if(int s, sa_family_t af)
 	return 0;
 }

+static void nl_route_print(struct nlmsghdr *nh, char *buf, size_t len)
+{
+	struct rtmsg *rtm = (struct rtmsg *)NLMSG_DATA(nh);
+	struct rtattr *rta;
+	size_t na, n;
+
+	for (rta = RTM_RTA(rtm), na = RTM_PAYLOAD(nh); RTA_OK(rta, na);
+	     rta = RTA_NEXT(rta, na)) {
+		char addrbuf[INET6_ADDRSTRLEN];
+
+		if (rta->rta_type == RTA_DST || rta->rta_type == RTA_GATEWAY) {
+			n = snprintf(buf, len, "%s: %s ",
+				     rta->rta_type == RTA_DST ? "dst" : "gw",
+				     inet_ntop(rtm->rtm_family, RTA_DATA(rta),
+					       addrbuf, sizeof(addrbuf)));
+			buf += n;
+			len -= n;
+		}
+	}
+}
+
 /**
  * nl_route_get_def_multipath() - Get lowest-weight route from nexthop list
  * @rta:	Routing netlink attribute with type RTA_MULTIPATH
@@ -655,8 +676,13 @@ int nl_route_dup(int s_src, unsigned int ifi_src,
 			rc = nl_do(s_dst, nh, RTM_NEWROUTE,
 				   (flags & ~NLM_F_DUMP_FILTERED) | NLM_F_CREATE,
 				   nh->nlmsg_len);
-			if (rc < 0 && rc != -ENETUNREACH && rc != -EEXIST)
+			if (rc < 0 && rc != -ENETUNREACH && rc != -EEXIST) {
+				char buf[BUFSIZ];
+
+				nl_route_print(nh, buf, BUFSIZ);
+				err("Failed to copy route, %s", buf);
 				return rc;
+			}
 		}
 	}

```

then start pasta stand-alone on your system (`./pasta --config-net`) and see what route it actually fails to copy to the container? Thanks.
